{{Infobox language |name=’Beli |nativename=Jur Beli |states=[[South Sudan]] |speakers=65,000 |date=2009 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Central Sudanic languages|Central Sudanic]] |fam3=[[Bongo–Bagirmi languages|Bongo–Bagirmi]] |fam4=[[Bongo–Baka languages|Bongo–Baka]] |iso3=blm |glotto=beli1257 |glottorefname=Beli (Sudan) }} '''’Beli''', or '''Jur Beli''', is a [[Central Sudanic language]] spoken by the Beli and Sopi people of [[South Sudan]].
