'''Clerk of the chapel''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] title for an assistant [[shop steward]] representing [[trade union]] members in the [[printing]] industry.

The clerk of the chapel assists the [[father of the chapel]]. The clerk acts as secretary at meetings, takes and reads minutes, collects subscriptions and dues, and reports on chapel activities.

