'''Jur Modo''', also known as ''Jur'' or ''Modo'', is a [[Central Sudanic language]] spoken by the [[Jur Modo people]] of [[South Sudan]]. Dialects are Lori, Modo (Jur Modo, Modo Lali), Wira, Wetu. It is a [[tonal language]].

