{{notability|Biographies|date=November 2015}}
'''Zaradachet Hajo''', (or '''Zerdeşt Haco''') (born 1950) is a [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] writer, linguist and researcher, born in [[Syria]] in 1950. He has studied linguistics, [[German language|German]] and [[Iranian languages]] at the Free University of [[Berlin]], and wrote his doctoral thesis on [[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian language]] studies. Since 1982, he has been teaching at the universities of Berlin, [[Bremen (city)|Bremen]] and [[Hamburg]]. He has been the president of the [[Kurdish language|Kurdish]] chapter of the literary organization [[International PEN|PEN]] since 1998.
==Works== Zaradachet Hajo has been involved in the translation of the [[Bible]] into [[Kurdish language|Kurdish]] language. He has also published many linguistic essays and papers in [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] newspapers and journals. He has published a collection of his poems in a book titled ''Songs from the Exile''.
